&gt; I&#39;m no JSON-LD expert at all. So there are maybe some errors in the
&gt; markup above. Furthermore, I guess, this example can even be shortened.
&gt; A hyperlink relation is simply expressed via its coercion (as pointed
&gt; by
&gt; Markus), e.g., &quot;ex:customer&quot;: &quot;/customer/jen&quot; would be a link relation.
&gt; An &#39;embedded resource&#39; is in this example, e.g., &quot;/orders/124&quot;. The
&gt; JSON-LD knowledge representation is even more expressive, since it
&gt; includes resource and literal types (which, I guess, are optional).
&gt; All property and resource type definitions should be de-referencable
&gt; themselves.
